originalText.text: Came here on New Year’s Eve where we had a reservation for 530. We were seated immediately and the staff ready with decorations to boot for New Year’s Eve dinner service. The hostess offered to hang our coats, and we were immediately guided to a table for two closer towards the front of the restaurant. The food was delicious. The ambience was better than I expected, as I have only seen this restaurant on television when YouTube or the likes was interviewing either the executive chef (who was there this night!) or the owner Marcus Samuelson. The only part that I was on the fence about is, I think they had so much staff at dinner service it seemed excessive. We were asked several times throughout the night if everything was OK and or did we want to order anything else. It often interrupted conversation and the flow of the meal. our waitress was amazing and really sweet. It was everyone I guess who is helping her to ensure our dining experience was seamless seemed a bit intrusive. Overall, I definitely will want to experience this restaurant again as the food and service was top tier AND they had a pretty dope DJ experience and large enough seating for tables of five or more. Go here!!

originalText.text:
Went here for dinner recently and had pretty good food. Everything was flavorful and different. We would have ordered more drinks, but the service was subpar that they never asked for another round. Other than that I enjoyed the flavors.
We ordered the bread basket which was good but was overwhelmingly sweet for me. I was looking for something that will mellow down the buttery and sweet feeling. Nevertheless it was still good. Loved the butter and the tomato relish. We also ordered the market curry and snapper - very flavorful.

originalText.text: This was a nice place. Food was excellent.  I didn't really know what a lot of it was honestly so I went on their Instagram. There were photos of the food but I feel like the photographer may not have caught the food in a great light. What was brought out wasn't exactly what I got from the photo. (Did not try ALL dishes so may have just picked a lucky one) but the drinks were great and our service was amazing. Definately recommend the blue corn bread and the crab toast !

originalText.text: The skin on a fillet of black sea bass is seared to a pale-gold crisp before the fish is perched over hard-shell clams and purple potatoes. Underneath is a seafood-corn broth. Both the sauce and the bass are flavored with dawadawa, ground African locust beans, which acts as an intensifier in this dish, something like miso.

originalText.text: Looking at the reviews and pics of this place, I was really excited for the experience. And of course I had high expectations from a Marcus Samuelsson establishment. And for the most part it did not disappoint. The ambiance was warm and inviting and the attention to detail was beautiful. Service was attentive despite it being a little busy. My friend and I sat at the bar and had a full dining experience. First, the cornbread appetizer was a perfect start to dinner. My only slight disappointment was with the pasta dish. The amount of shrimp and crab wasn’t much and left a lot to be desired. And my friend thought the lamb meatballs were just ok. I didn’t try it but he said the sauce/gravy was rather thick. And the red snapper dish was rather tasty, I just would have preferred the full brussell sprouts instead of just the charred outer leaves. But there were other dishes that I wanted to try so I would go back again for something different.
